The elements of paper flower making mainly consist of ⁠
⁠
🌸 the selection crepe paper color and weight ⁠
🌸 wiring your petals, leaves or stem⁠
🌸 the coloration you apply to the petals, leaves and stem⁠

The final element is thinking of the form of your paper flower. What is form? It’s the shape and size you want to create your paper flower. Is it a singular flower that will stand alone, or will it be in an arrangement? If so, is it the star of the arrangement, or will it play a supporting role?⁠

How does proportion plays into creating your paper flowers?⁠
⁠
Understanding how big or small to cut your petals or leaves along with how many bloom to make will make your paper flower making process much easier and more pleasing to the eye. ⁠
⁠
Know that working with odd numbers loveral ooks much better. Using ratios like: 3:5 or 3:5:8, which is known as the #thegoldenratio or some knows it as the #fibonaccisequence⁠
⁠
Consider making a bloom that is 8 inch tall, the bloom head 5 inch wide and 3 inch deep and let me know what you think!⁠

Happy New Year, dear friends! 

2022 had so many amazing highs and lows.

Some amazing highs - working with some generous and lovely clients. Joining a mastermind to expand my mind and how I view my business. Seeing my family, meeting and hugging people I have not seen since Covid. Creating some beautiful flowers. Creating memories that will last a lifetime and beyond. 

My low happened just a few weeks ago when my grandfather of 94 years young passed away. I say young because his heart was so strong and beautiful. He had a beautiful soul. He was witty, kind, resourceful, and intelligent. I was so glad I got to see him several times last year and be there when he was laid to rest. I ended my 2022 quiet and with family. It was what I needed. 

2023. I am starting the year with an intention—an intention to treasure my family and friend a bit more. 

This year I plan to take less commission for work. I’m stepping back a little bit to rest my hands, focus on my family, teach more, and be more present instead of looking at my phone. 

My word for the year is INTENTION, with a purpose.

Peonies. It’s so short lived, but what a majestic bloom this is. 

Depending on which peony you made, you will either focus on the petals like a bomb peony, or if you are doing a coral charm, it’s the color and that fantastic center. 

My tip for you is to study this bloom, Take it apart and examine how the petals are attached to the center. You will notice that not every petal is the same, and the color gradation is so beautiful. 

You are going to have to sacrifice a few peonies and see how the peony changes from day to day, especially the coral charm, where it’s a deep beautiful red-pink, and how it fades to a soft pink vanilla color. It’s so fascinating to me how the peony changes from day to day.

Why am I still making paper flowers after eight years?⁠
⁠
It comes from that feeling I have when sitting down with crepe paper, a pair of scissors, and tacky glue. It’s the inner quiet joy that I find when I’m concentrating on cutting the perfect petal and then figuring out how to paint or manipulate it to curve a certain way.⁠
⁠
Over the years, I feel like I have stayed true to my style, but my techniques have evolved and my confidence has grown.

2. Be consistent and authentic in your content: Consistency is key when building a community on Instagram. Post regularly and make sure your content is authentic and aligned with your brand values. This will help your audience know what to expect from you and build trust in your brand.

What I have is a can do attitude.⁠
⁠
I think it’s an essential trait if you work for yourself because you do have to wear so many hats.⁠
⁠
Hat 1️⃣ accountant - knowing your numbers is so incredibly important. With numbers, you know how to calculate your pieces, so you make can pay yourself. YOUR LABOR IS NOT FREE. Please repeat that! Your time is just as valuable as anyone else, and please remember that. Know your overhead cost, keep track of your expenses, and know your bottom line.⁠
⁠
Hat 2️⃣ marketer/brand ambassador - can you sell yourself to others? I think this one is a hard one for females. We have always been taught don’t toot your own horn—people will see your value. Unfortunately, this is not the case. If you can’t talk about yourself, get advocates for yourself, they can be your best friend, a wing woman when you go to events. I always find it easier to advocate for my friend than for myself—why is that? ⁠
⁠
Hat 3️⃣ writer/graphic designer - I  found these two roles work side by side. Knowing how to write the copy that goes with your image or promotions for your work— to sell your work or workshops if you teach. Knowing how to soft sell without selling is a tricky thing. I think, as females, we don’t ever want to be pushy or consider sales. Why is that so hard to sell ourselves and our work? Why is it so hard to toot our own horn?⁠
⁠
What other hats do you wear while running your business? ⁠

With tax season looming ahead, don't forget these expenses you need to track and deduct from your business. Also, I am not a tax accountant, but this is from my experiences and what I have been doing to deduct my expenses.⁠
⁠
Are you ready? Here are some common expenses that you need to be aware of⁠
⁠
1. Business supplies and equipment - your phone or camera where you are recording those videos or taking those pictures to promote your work⁠
⁠
2. Office rent and utilities - if you have a dedicated work area to create your artwork, you can calculate how much space that is 5 feet by 5 feet or a whole room plus, don't forget your internet connection and phone bill!⁠
⁠

This German paper crepe was washed with a diluted acrylic crepe that I had matched to a Pantone color the client wanted from my experience instead of painting the paper with acrylic paint, which by the way, coats the paper with colored “plastic” and stiffened the paper. 

I wanted my paper to maintain its crepe paper softness and crepe. I know washing it will also change the paper—both in color and texture.

✂️📜 Homemade Crepe Paper: Create Something Unique and Sustainable! 🌿💫⁠
⁠
Looking for a unique crepe paper option? Why not try making your own? Homemade crepe paper allows you to repurpose old scraps and experiment with something new. Let's dive into the creative process of making your own crepe paper and unleash your imagination! 🎨✂️⁠
⁠
Here are the basic steps to create your homemade crepe paper:⁠
⁠
1️⃣ Mix the paper scraps with water and beat them using a blender to create a pulp.⁠
2️⃣ Pour the pulp into a flat pan, ensuring an even distribution.⁠
3️⃣ Insert a screen into the pan, then carefully lift it out, allowing the excess water to drain.⁠
4️⃣ Blot the paper pulp with a cloth or towel to remove additional water.⁠
5️⃣ Roll the paper gently to further extract excess water.⁠
6️⃣ Allow the paper to dry completely.⁠
⁠
The resulting homemade crepe paper will be thicker than other varieties, but it retains its beauty and can prove useful for a wide range of projects. Let your imagination run wild as you explore the endless possibilities of this unique material. ♻️🌸⁠

I want to share a conversation with someone who worked at Meta. I had a call with them a few weeks ago, and I had 30 minutes to ask as many questions as possible.

And let me tell you, I had a ton! I ran over my time. 

I’ll break down some answers and confirmation of what they said.

I know this one was at the top of my list. Is hashtags in play, and YES it is. They told me to always use at least 5 to 8 hashtags in your post. But no more than 8 and no less than 5.

Always use your one hashtag that is identified to you. Mine is #pinkandposey I have been using this one pretty consistently and now have over 1000 tags 🥳🥳🥳

Another hashtag they told me was to use a description from your video or photo that is UNRELATED to what your main image is about. For example, instead of using #daisyflower use #whitebackground or #whiteflowers or #oopsadaisy

Here’s the ranking that is super important when posting on Instagram for IG to share it with other viewers, followers and unfollowers. Video is still King!

1. Reels with trending music ( ↗️ )
2. Carousel of photos and videos
3. Post of one image

But it all comes down to being consistent and authentic with your audience and how often you are posting. 

Be CONSISTENT. If you only post once weekly, set an alarm and always post on Monday at 8 am. Choose the day and time that works best for you. Use another IG app to help stay consistent, like @latermedia  or @planoly (they highly recommended it)

“There is no perfection, only beautiful versions of brokenness.” By Shannon L Alder 

Everyone has flaws. I have flaws. I’m afraid to upset others, and that limits what I want to do. I hate confrontation and conflicts. I used to have the most challenging time to speak up for myself.

Recently, I have been going to the gym and had an uncomfortable moment. It was with the trainer who was training a small group. He was a man, and I have been mulling it over and thought if a woman said this, would I have felt uncomfortable too? And the answer was yes.  So what happened: we were doing a modified push up, and he was telling us how to do it properly, and he was telling us where to put our hands on the ground and how to push up in the correct form. He said to put our hands by our breasts and nipples.  I was actually shocked. The girl that was with me gave a nervous giggle. It made us both uncomfortable, and we did not speak up.  I wished at that moment I did, and I regretted not saying anything. I’m not a prune, but I had never heard a trainer use those words in a gym.
